<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Privacy Policy — Daily</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Privacy policy for Daily, a private journaling app for iPhone.">
  <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/assets/daily-icon.png">
  <link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="/assets/daily-icon.png">
</head>
<body>
  <main class="page">
    <a href="/daily" class="back">&larr; Daily</a>

    <h1>Privacy Policy for Daily</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: July 10, 2026</p>

    <p>Daily is a personal journaling app. Your privacy is important to us.</p>

    <h2>Data Collection</h2>
    <p>Daily has no servers and does not collect, store, or transmit any personal data. All journal entries, photos, and attachments are stored locally on your device.</p>

    <h2>Voice Transcription</h2>
    <p>Voice notes are transcribed using Apple's Speech framework. On devices that support it, transcription happens entirely on-device. On devices that do not, audio may be processed by Apple's servers under <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/">Apple's privacy policy</a>. Daily itself never receives this data.</p>

    <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>Daily does not use any third-party analytics, advertising, or tracking services.</p>

    <h2>Biometric Data</h2>
    <p>Daily offers an optional Face ID lock feature. Biometric authentication is handled entirely by your device's operating system. Daily does not access, store, or process any biometric data.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>If you have questions about this privacy policy, you can reach me at <a href="mailto:3moreno.jordan@gmail.com">3moreno.jordan@gmail.com</a></p>
  </main>

  <footer class="footer">
    <span>&copy; <span id="year"></span> Jordan Moreno</span>
  </footer>

  <script>
    document.getElementById('year').textContent = new Date().getFullYear().toString();
  </script>
</body>
</html>

